Trump designated Saudi Arabia a major non-NATO ally during a historic White House dinner with Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman, marking 80 years of relations.
Nassau County Executive Bruce Blakeman slammed Gov. Kathy Hochul's potential corporate tax increase, warning it would be a "disaster" for New York's economy.
Trump promises $2,000 dividend payments to Americans from tariff revenue by mid-2026, as collections surge to $37.5 billion in fiscal 2026.
President Donald Trump explained on Monday his raspy voice resulted from heated trade discussions with a foreign country who sought to renegotiate a deal with him.

The Trump administration stays silent as a $100 million Ukraine corruption scandal rocks Zelenskyy's government, prompting senior official resignations.
The FBI director said China has agreed on a plan to curb the flow of chemicals used to produce fentanyl. (Credit: NBC Pool)
U.S. Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent joins 'Fox & Friends' to discuss the shutdown’s financial impact on the economy and outlines how rising wages and tax relief could help jump-start recovery.
President Donald Trump discusses the government shutdown, affordability and 50-year mortgages on 'The Ingraham Angle.'
Louvre Museum reportedly used "Louvre" as password for surveillance system during $100M jewel heist. Learn how weak passwords put even famous institutions at risk.
Wholesalers in the wine industry warn that prices could be rising soon. Tariffs have impacted both importers of foreign wines and wineries at home dealing with higher operating costs.

Former vice presidential deputy national security advisor Steve Yates traces China's history of poisoning Americans and commends the Trump administration's first step to decoupling from its 'stranglehold' on 'The Ingraham Angle.'
Secretary of War Pete Hegseth announced on Thursday that a strike on a suspected drug-trafficking vessel killed three "narco-terrorists."
Putin orders nuclear test preparations after Trump announces U.S. will resume testing. Russia vows proportionate response to American nuclear program moves.
Mexican President Claudia Sheinbaum is pressing charges against a man who groped and tried to kiss her during a public appearance in Mexico City.
London's "Mind the Grab" campaign is sparking outrage as critics slam officials for blaming victims instead of stopping phone thieves on Oxford Street.
U.S. Trade Representative Amb. Jamieson Greer addresses the legal uniqueness of the word ‘tariff’ on ‘The Ingraham Angle.’
'Special Report' panelists analyze President Donald Trump's exclusive interview, the election results, the debate over doing away with the filibuster and more.
Supreme Court justices expressed skepticism about Donald Trump's use of emergency law to impose global tariffs during oral arguments Wednesday.
'Special Report' panelists discuss how Americans are feeling the impacts of the government shutdown and the legality of President Donald Trump's tariffs.
Fox News contributor Karl Rove breaks down President Donald Trump's recent trade negotiations with China and more on 'One Nation.'
Fox News host recaps President Donald Trump's Asia tour and trade deals and questions how anyone could not see it as a success on 'One Nation.'
White House National Economic Council Director Kevin Hassett discusses President Donald Trump's trade deal with China, the government shutdown and more on 'Sunday Night in America.'

Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent joins Fox News 'Sunday' to highlight progress from President Donald Trump’s Asia trip, including China trade negotiations, rare earth supply chain deals, fentanyl enforcement and pending tariff cases.
Trump tariff case before Supreme Court could reshape presidential power. Global trade uncertainty grows as justices weigh emergency authority limits this Wednesday.
Jesse Watters recaps President Donald Trump’s Asia trip and praises him for his stamina amid a turbulent flight home on ‘Jesse Watters Primetime.’

'The Five' co-hosts discuss President Donald Trump's meeting with Chinese President Xi Jinping.
